Based on the code snippet you've provided and your description of the issue, there are a few potential reasons why the HTML content might not be correctly loading into the Quill editor:

1. Fetching the HTML file: The `fetchHTMLContent` function uses a relative URL path to try and load the content. Make sure that the path is correct and the server is properly configured to serve the file.

2. Incorrect handling of Quill Editor content: The Quill editor uses a Delta format for its content, so setting HTML directly via `quill.setContents()` will not work because `setContents` expects a Delta, not an HTML string.

3. Using the Quill editor in a non-standard way: Quill expects a container element to initialize, not a textarea. You should create a div with a specific ID or class that Quill will transform into an editor.

To fix these issues, make the following changes:

Replace the `<textarea id="Body" name="Body"></textarea>` with the following div container to correctly initialize Quill:
```html
<div id="Body" class="quill-editor"></div>
```

Use `quill.clipboard.dangerouslyPasteHTML()` to set the HTML content instead of `quill.setContents()`. This method can handle HTML content properly.

Here's an updated version of the script section with the changes reflected:

```html
@section Scripts {
    <!-- Include the Quill library -->
    <script src="https://cdn.quilljs.com/1.3.6/quill.js"></script>

    <!-- Initialize Quill for the email body -->
    <script>
        // Fetch the HTML content from the file
        async function fetchHTMLContent() {
